questions.explanationMd:
**express-validator** workflow:

```js
const { body, validationResult } = require('express-validator');

app.post('/register', [
  body('email').isEmail(),                    // ✅ Option A
  body('password').isLength({ min: 8 }),       // ✅ Option C (check also works)
], (req, res) => {
  const errors = validationResult(req);        // ✅ Option B
  if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
    return res.status(400).json({ errors: errors.array() });
  }
  // proceed...
});
```

Option D is **wrong** — you must explicitly call `validationResult(req)` and handle errors yourself. express-validator does **not** automatically send error responses.
